node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text:
When reaching for a new aperitivo bitter, you might ask, “Does this stand alone? Does it bring something new to the table?” In the case of Carpano’s new Botanic Bitter (@carpanobotanicbitter #punchpartner), bartenders are answering with a resounding yes. Find out why they’re turning to the latest release from the storied 18th century Italian brand and how they use it in cocktails via the link in our profile.⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 31, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: What happens when the bitter, bubbly, low-ABV spritz template meets the Zombie’s famously layered build? At @dantenewyorkcity they seamlessly combine the two into a 12-ingredient cocktail that feels firmly rooted to both. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 31, 2021. May be an image of drink and text.

node.text: In our recent tasting of more than 70 ready-to-drink cocktails (RTDs), it became clear quite quickly to the panelists that the proposition of a canned cocktail is not as simple as putting a cocktail in a can. It takes an understanding of how extracts, acids and clarification impact flavor to translate the experience of an à la minute creation into a shelf-stable product. With no shortage of zeitgeisty, eye-catching canned cocktails on the shelves, there’s never been a better moment to parse the good from the bad. Head to the link in our profile for the cans (and bottle!) that left us wanting another sip. Big thanks to our panel of tasters: @chloefrechette, @taliabaiocchi, @drinksat6, @schrammplate. #drinkpunch

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 30, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: The Margarita’s minimal formula—simply tequila, orange liqueur, lime and sweetener—makes it one of the most adaptable recipes in the cocktail canon. While mezcal-spiked variations are frequently spotted today, that wasn't the case when @mightyschneidey started offering it at @employeesonlyny. Get the recipe for the New York bar’s ever-popular, signature, smoky serve via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 30, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text: You can't go wrong with a Campari Sour. The simple sour, which leans on both grapefruit and lime for the citrus component, is a low-proof option built on the Italian red bitter, because, well, why not. Get the aperitivo hour-ready recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro ⁠⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by PUNCH on August 29, 2021 tagging @maracujabk. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: “There’s nothing better than a frozen Margarita on a humid New York day,” says @erikplambeck, co-owner of the Brooklyn bar @maracujabk. Among the Frosés and Frieslings, pineapple-garnished Piña Coladas, multilayered Miami Vices and technicolor Cosmopolitans, the frozen Margarita has brought its A game. It’s a classic for a reason, and one that adapts like a chameleon to a splash of fruit purée or a spicy hot-pepper kick. But a crop of new-school frozen Margaritas takes creative license and stretches the boundaries beyond the expected via the addition of Spanish fortified wines, Italian amari, herbal French liqueurs and myriad combinations of spices, syrups and fruit that just might stick around long after summer ends. Head to the link in our profile to read @btparsons’ latest and get new school recipes from @columbiaroom, @thaidiner, @horseinn, @publicrecordsnyc, and @maracujabk. #drinkpunch 📷: @@brianabalducciphoto

node.text:
The tried-and-true combination of spirit and cola has likely been a gateway for many to the world of cocktails. Whether that spirit is whiskey or rum, or perhaps something a bit more localized and esoteric, these mixed drinks are go-to cocktails for a reason: They always work. And today this combo is getting a serious upgrade with introduction of new, craft colas in the market. Head to the link in our profile where top distillers making rye, fernet and rum describe the artistry of their spirits, alongside thoughtful recipes for mixing their products with Fever-Tree’s new Distillers Cola.⁠
#punchpartner @fevertree_usa⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PUNCH on August 28, 2021. May be an image of drink and indoor.

node.text: It’s the simplest cocktails that inspire the highest degree of obsession. Such is the case with @latitude29nola's Daiquiri, which took 18 months of experimentation to perfect. In an effort to cut down on dilution, @official_beachbumberry omits simple syrup, preferring instead to dissolve a mixture of cane sugar and turbinado sugar directly into fresh lime juice before shaking and straining with white rum and ice. Get the full recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @clairebangser

node.text: In @joshgoldman2's Paloma Rosa the Mexican classic goes floral. Currently on the menu at LA's @barcalola, the highball is made with a house blend of two rose liqueurs mixed with grapefruit and a spiced elixir. The finishing touch is a rosy half-rim of Himalayan pink salt and a spritz of rose water, which Goldman keeps in an atomizer to spray over the top of the drink. Bright and balanced, it's floral without veering into perfume territory. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @dylanandjeni

node.text: A simple mix of Plymouth gin, Carpano bianco vermouth and Dolin dry vermouth, Phil Ward's subtle Martini variation gets a ghostly herbal aftertaste from shiso. To incorporated the herbaceous flavor, he lets the liquor sit upon a bed of shiso leaves for a minute before it is stirred over ice and strained into a shiso-rubbed glass. Head to the link in our profile to get the recipe for his Beefsteak Martini. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Based on tiki baron Don the Beachcomber’s 1941 recipe for Navy Grog, @matthewsbelanger's Shore Leave Spritz stays true to its maritime origins but lightens the usual three-ounce rum base in favor of a small dose of navy-strength gin and Cocchi Americano. Resulting in the sort of spicy, juicy cocktail you’d want to drink while on dry land. Head to the link in our bio for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @dylanandjeni⁠

node.text: Ken Ellis, bouncer-turned-bartender, has held court at Chicago’s iconic Rainbo Club (@real_rainboclub) for nearly four decades. The OG bartender sits down with @robertosimonson to talk about how he got started in the industry, his second career in hand-stitched quilt portraits and what he's learned from 44 years behind the bar—via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @mattandsarahhaas
